Rest Assured is Java DSL (domain specific language)library for writing test for restful API.
jsonpath, gpath,xmlpath used to extract the body from json response.


then.asserthThat.ContentType(ContentType.json)

or 

then.asserthThat.ContentType("application/json")

hamcrest matchers :

body("$places[0].'place name'", equalTo("gwalior"));

xpath path for html

xmlpath for xml

jsonpath for json (path expression langauge for json)

Rest Assured uses GPath notation.

hasItem
hasSize

jsonpath cant be used to extract or querying the xml response.instead use xmlpath.

wiremock : create the similar behaviour or API.


//FROM RESPONSE : LAST mode ( places[-1])

//how to get attribute value from response using xmlpath 
$ response.places.place[1].@attributename


POJO: Plain old java object
deserilization : json response to pojo 


serilization : java object to json request body 

